The paper deals with the problem of joint channel estimation and data detection in wireless systems with large antenna arrays, which is a common topic in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and communications (cs.COMM). However, given the focus on massive MIMO systems and the use of maximum likelihood algorithms, cs.IT and cs.COMM are the most likely sub-categories.
